"{\"uid\": \"rappler.com-sports-tom-daley-announces-retirement-after-silver-paris-olympics-2024\", \"text\": \"  SUMMARY  This is AI generated summarization, which may have errors. For context, always refer to the full article.  ICON. Britain's diving men's synchronized 10m platform silver medalist Tom Daley returns to London.  John Sibley/Action Images/Reuters  Britain's five-time Olympic diving medalist\\u00a0Tom\\u00a0Daley\\u00a0is retiring from the sport, he said on Monday, August 12, as he returned from the Paris Games where he won\\u00a0silver\\u00a0in the men's synchronized 10-meter event together with Noah Williams.  Having stepped away from the sport after the Tokyo Olympics in 2021,\\u00a0Daley\\u00a0made a return last year at the request of his older son, and his appearance in Paris made him the first British diver to compete at five Olympics.  \\\"It was emotional at the end, up there on the platform, knowing it was going to be my last competitive dive,\\\" the 30-year-old\\u00a0Daley\\u00a0told British Vogue.  \\\"But I have to make the decision at some point, and it feels like the right time. It's the right time to call it a day.\\\"  Daley, whose popularity grew even more after he came out as gay in 2013, had won the Olympic gold medal in the men's synchronized 10-meter platform event at the Tokyo Games.  \\\"I am really happy with how everything's gone,\\\" an emotional\\u00a0Daley\\u00a0told the BBC.  \\\"It's always hard when you say goodbye to your sport. Lots of things to process, but I think it's the right time. This year felt like such a bonus and I got to compete in front of my family, my kids. I got to be flag bearer. So yeah, bucket list ticked off on every occasion.\\\"- Rappler.com  How does this make you feel?  follow us          \"}"